JobSummary:
The VA Maine Healthcare System is seeking a Service Chief (Radiologist) who will be responsible for planning, developing and directing administrative and clinical functions of the Radiology / Nuclear Medicine Service.&#160; Body Imaging, Neuroadiology, and/or VIR Fellowship with Certificate of Added Qualification (CAQ) is desirable.&#160; Training and skills in Nuclear Medicine is a plus.&#160; Candidate must be Board Certified in Radiology.
The Service Chief reports directly to the Chief of Staff.&#160; (S)He will supervise the daily activities and coordinate coverage for the Radiology Service, be responsible for overall operation, oversight and performance measures of this busy department which provides a wide range of diagnostic and interventional procedures. The Service Chief provides administrative, clinical and programmatic leadership for the service to ensure achieved performance measures. Responsibilities also include membership in several facility committees and activities assigned by management.&#160; The role of this position is to provide patient care approximately 50% of the time and perform administrative duties during the remaining&#160;50%.&#160; Administrative and/or business experience in managing a budget and supervising personnel is preferred.&#160; Must be familiar with PACS and Voice Recognition dictation systems.&#160; Must be computer literate and possess basic typing skills.&#160;Competitive salaries, generous leave package, health & life insurance benefits, and retirement benefits.&#160; Additionally, the right candidate will experience the sense of patriotism and pride associated with working with veterans.&#160; The incumbent is eligible to participate in a pension program as well as a matching Thrift Savings Plan which is similar to a 401K.&#160; Candidates with prior military experience may be able to combine their accrued military retirement credit with VA pension benefits.&#160;
